Wreckage of the vehicles involved in the Kilifi road accident. [Marion Kithi, Standard]  Several people are feared dead following a crash involving a matatu and a lorry at Matsangoni along the Mombasa-Malindi highway.  Confirming the accident to The Standard, Kilifi County Commissioner Kutswa Olaka said a rescue operation is underway.  "We are on a rescue mission and moving survivors to Kilifi District hospital…though as of now we can't ascertain the number of casualties,” he said.  Survivors have been taken to the Kilifi District hospital for treatment. More to follow…  By Patrick Beja | 2 days ago By Marion Kithi | 2 days ago By Patrick Beja | 7 days ago By Philip Mwakio | 9 days ago Subscribe to a 1-year plan and get a 50% discount before the 1st of January 2022!